# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package: 2. Materials Science
# By Simon Gravelle, Mark A. Tschopp, Jacob R. Gissinger, and Axel Kohlmeyer
# Tutorial 18: 3. A stepped TiO2 (110) surface -- charge redistribution at edges
#
# Same (110) slab as surface110.lmp, but wider, and with the top O-Ti2O2-O
# trilayer removed over half of the surface.  This carves two terraces
# joined by monatomic steps along [001].  Because the cut plane lies in the
# gap between trilayers and a trilayer is charge neutral, the deleted patch
# is exactly stoichiometric.  After relaxation, the charges at the step
# edges differ from both the flat terrace and the bulk -- local chemistry
# made visible by the charge-transfer potential.

# 1) Initialization
units metal
dimension 3
boundary p p s
atom_style charge

# 2) System definition (see surface110.lmp for the rotated-cell derivation)
lattice custom 1.0     a1 6.5062 0.0 0.0  a2 0.0 2.9646 0.0  a3 0.0 0.0 6.5062     basis 0.0    0.0  0.0    basis 0.5    0.0  0.5     basis 0.0    0.5  0.5    basis 0.5    0.5  0.0     basis 0.0    0.0  0.3048 basis 0.5    0.0  0.8048     basis 0.0    0.0  0.6952 basis 0.5    0.0  0.1952     basis 0.3048 0.5  0.5    basis 0.8048 0.5  0.0     basis 0.6952 0.5  0.5    basis 0.1952 0.5  0.0     origin 0.0 0.0 0.25
